it up with, "But I don't date 13-year-olds. "

1006
01:17:30,561 --> 01:17:33,291
Well, lucky for you, neither do I.

1007
01:17:33,864 --> 01:17:35,297
Cheers.

1008
01:17:35,466 --> 01:17:36,763
Cheers.

1009
01:17:46,876 --> 01:17:48,343
- Oh, I'm sorry.
- Hi.

1010
01:17:48,511 --> 01:17:51,912
Sorry. Oh, I can't do this, I'm sorry.
It's not you.

1011
01:17:52,082 --> 01:17:54,516
<i>Look at me, I'm shaking.
I don't know how to do this.</i>

1012
01:17:54,684 --> 01:17:57,175
Don't even know if I want to,
I haven't been held in...

1013
01:17:57,354 --> 01:18:01,380
Oh, never mind. I'm just screwed up.
I'm trouble. Yeah.

1014
01:18:01,790 --> 01:18:04,224
- I like trouble.
- Oh, no. Heh.

1015
01:18:04,393 --> 01:18:06,759
<i>I don't mean "cool Pulp Fiction" trouble...</i>

1016
01:18:06,929 --> 01:18:10,922
...I mean "mental case wacko" trouble.

1017
01:18:11,233 --> 01:18:15,635
I'm out of my league here. I mean,
I haven't had a new man in over 10 years.

1018
01:18:15,803 --> 01:18:17,930
I had this old one. I mean, he wasn't old.

1019
01:18:18,106 --> 01:18:20,631
He was just old to me
because I had him so often.

1020
01:18:20,808 --> 01:18:22,833
He was my husband, but he died.

1021
01:18:25,346 --> 01:18:27,837
Kissing him like that,
I'm not surprised, poor lad.

1022
01:18:38,759 --> 01:18:39,953
No, it's not gonna work.

1023
01:18:40,460 --> 01:18:44,920
