I really wanna buy, but they just don't fit.

1024
01:18:45,098 --> 01:18:46,827
Sorry.

1025
01:18:47,134 --> 01:18:51,661
All right then, how about
going barefoot for a while?

1026
01:19:19,330 --> 01:19:23,959
There's no man, alive or dead,
who's gonna fault you for living.

1027
01:19:25,102 --> 01:19:27,502
You're very sweet.

1028
01:19:29,373 --> 01:19:33,867
He was a good man, I reckon,
your man who died.

1029
01:19:34,578 --> 01:19:36,205
Yes...

1030
01:19:37,080 --> 01:19:39,071
...a very good man.

1031
01:19:47,123 --> 01:19:48,715
- William?
- Hmm?

1032
01:19:49,792 --> 01:19:53,421
Could you drive me to Enniskerry
in the morning?

1033
01:19:53,596 --> 01:19:54,995
Sure.

1034
01:19:55,498 --> 01:19:56,931
You got friends there?

1035
01:19:57,099 --> 01:19:59,828
Family. Sort of.

1036
01:20:00,302 --> 01:20:03,203
- In-laws. I should see them.
- Hmm.

1037
01:20:04,473 --> 01:20:07,101
What's their name? Maybe I know them.

1038
01:20:07,342 --> 01:20:08,775
The Kennedys.

1039
01:20:11,046 --> 01:20:13,640
Not Rose and Martin?

1040
01:20:14,049 --> 01:20:17,711
Yeah. You know them?

1041
01:20:22,122 --> 01:20:24,556
You're not Gerry's Holly?

1042
01:20:25,359 --> 01:20:26,383
What?

1043
01:20:26,727 --> 01:20:28,285
Oh...

1044
01:20:28,896 --> 01:20:30,989
