1075
01:22:21,802 --> 01:22:26,398
Starting back when we were terrors
running about at 5 and 6.

1076
01:22:28,275 --> 01:22:30,333
Oh, he made me laugh.

1077
01:22:30,509 --> 01:22:33,478
There was this time,
I don't remember how old we were...

1078
01:22:33,646 --> 01:22:36,080
...probably, you know, 10, 11.

1079
01:22:36,849 --> 01:22:38,407
We jumped on a train...

1080
01:23:29,832 --> 01:23:34,599
We received those packages you sent.
Come in. Come in.

1081
01:23:40,609 --> 01:23:41,667
Martin?

1082
01:23:43,311 --> 01:23:44,938
Look who it is.

1083
01:23:45,113 --> 01:23:48,048
Oh, well, look at that.

1084
01:23:48,216 --> 01:23:50,047
Come here, dear.

1085
01:23:50,252 --> 01:23:52,516
So nice to see you.

1086
01:23:53,288 --> 01:23:56,552
He was always one for writing.
Wasn't he?

1087
01:23:56,724 --> 01:23:58,123
Should've gone professional.

1088
01:23:58,292 --> 01:24:01,352
No. He did it for the love of it, Martin.

1089
01:24:01,896 --> 01:24:04,091
Now, where is it?

1090
01:24:04,365 --> 01:24:05,855
Oh, here it is.

1091
01:24:06,033 --> 01:24:10,197
"When Holly visits, take her
to my fort in the back yard...

1092
01:24:10,371 --> 01:24:11,997
...and give her this envelope. "

1093
01:24:12,505 --> 01:24:15,099
He knew that I'd come visit you?

1094
01:24:15,408 --> 01:24:19,037
Hmm. Suppose he did. Heh. Martin.

1095
01:24:19,612 --> 01:24:21,045
All right.

1096
01:24:25,485 --> 01:24:28,976
It's not really a fort,
it's just a stone wall.

1097
01:24:29,154 --> 01:24:31,281
He used to call it that when he was little.

1098
01:24:33,459 --> 01:24:36,257
He goes on about other things...

1099
01:24:36,695 --> 01:24:38,219
...lovely things.

1100
01:24:40,265 --> 01:24:44,599
He hadn't much strength in the end
though, did he?

1101
01:24:46,237 --> 01:24:49,900
Makes me sick to think
we weren't there when he died...

1102
01:24:50,074 --> 01:24:51,098
...for the funeral.

1103
01:24:51,275 --> 01:24:53,869
But you could hardly walk
just after your operation.

1104
01:24:54,545 --> 01:24:58,743
Maybe you'll come and visit us a bit more
now that he's gone, eh?

1105
01:24:58,983 --> 01:25:01,008
Martin, don't put that on her.

1106
01:25:01,185 --> 01:25:03,345
You're under no obligation.

1107
01:25:03,520 --> 01:25:06,546
It's not like we're blood family.

1108
01:25:07,190 --> 01:25:09,283
I'd like to come visit.

1109
01:25:09,459 --> 01:25:13,327
And I'm sorry we didn't in the past. L...

1110
01:25:14,231 --> 01:25:17,962
I just thought you were angry with me
for taking Gerry away.

1111
01:25:18,135 --> 01:25:21,035
- She wanted you dead, you know.
- Martin, don't you dare!

1112
01:25:21,203 --> 01:25:23,364
No, I don't blame you.

1113
01:25:23,539 --> 01:25:26,975
You know, my mother, she never
quite got over the idea either.

1114
01:25:27,143 --> 01:25:31,637
Yeah, well, you were both so young.
And it happened too fast.

1115
01:25:33,449 --> 01:25:38,010
But Gerry loved you. I saw that.

1116
01:25:38,586 --> 01:25:40,520
I saw that.

1117
01:25:46,728 --> 01:25:50,061
<i>To my Galway Girl:
You're an angel for seeing my folks.</i>

1118
01:25:50,231 --> 01:25:55,133
<i>I told you my mom didn't hate your guts.
Well, you know, anymore.</i>

1119
01:25:55,736 --> 01:26:00,196
<i>You are now standing in my fort
where I did all my big thinking.</i>

1120
01:26:00,374 --> 01:26:05,835
<i>This is where I stood thinking about you
after the very first time we met.</i>

1121
01:26:15,254 --> 01:26:17,950
<i>You didn't look real to me at first.</i>

1122
01:26:18,124 --> 01:26:20,991
<i>I never saw so many colors
on one girl before...</i>

1123
01:26:21,160 --> 01:26:23,993
<i>...but you looked like
you belonged out there, all right.</i>

1124
01:26:24,163 --> 01:26:26,495
<i>You and all your colors.</i>

1125
01:26:26,699 --> 01:26:29,826
<i>Do you remember
the first thing you ever said to me?</i>

1126
01:26:30,001 --> 01:26:31,525
I'm lost.

1127
01:26:31,703 --> 01:26:35,070
<i>Oh, you didn't look lost, not to me.</i>

1128
01:26:35,240 --> 01:26:37,435
So, what are you looking for out here?

1129
01:26:37,609 --> 01:26:40,635
Wicklow Mountains National Park?

1130
01:26:41,980 --> 01:26:45,938
Wicklow Mountains National Park.
Tell me, how long you been walking for?

1131
01:26:46,116 --> 01:26:47,481
A few hours.

1132
01:26:47,651 --> 01:26:51,678
Well, you've probably been in
the national park for a few hours, then.

1133
01:26:51,989 --> 01:26:53,889
Oh, my God.

1134
01:26:54,258 --> 01:26:55,589
This is a park?

1135
01:26:55,759 --> 01:26:57,386
Uh-huh.

1136
01:26:58,963 --> 01:27:00,123
Oh.

1137
01:27:00,297 --> 01:27:01,661
It's so cold!

1138
01:27:01,831 --> 01:27:04,095
The paper said it was gonna be warm.

1139
01:27:04,267 --> 01:27:08,260
It is warm. I know you're lost, but
you do know you're in Ireland, don't you?

1140
01:27:10,173 --> 01:27:13,370
Well, I better head back. Heh.

1141
01:27:13,676 --> 01:27:20,239
- And where is that?
- I'm staying at a B and B in Dunlougahairy.

1142
01:27:20,415 --> 01:27:23,748
Dunlagohairy?
No, I think you mean Dún Laoghaire.

1143
01:27:23,919 --> 01:27:27,787
- Heh-heh. You're kidding?
- No. Would I lie to you?

1144
01:27:29,391 --> 01:27:32,588
- Dún Laoghaire?
- Dún Laoghaire.

1145
01:27:34,763 --> 01:27:37,754
Okay. Thanks.

1146
01:27:37,965 --> 01:27:39,592
<i>You're grand.</i>

1147
01:27:40,768 --> 01:27:42,998
But you're going the wrong way,
you know.

1148
01:27:48,843 --> 01:27:50,071
That way?

1149
01:27:50,244 --> 01:27:51,802
Okay.

1150
01:27:51,978 --> 01:27:54,970
I think you quite enjoy this getting lost,
don't you?

1151
01:27:55,882 --> 01:28:00,080
You know, actually,
I don't mind so much, not here.

1152
01:28:00,787 --> 01:28:02,277
So how did you come to be here?

1153
01:28:02,455 --> 01:28:06,414
Oh, on my way home, college trip.
We started in Greece.

1154
01:28:06,593 --> 01:28:09,584
Jesus, that's a long walk.
That's a bad joke.

1155
01:28:09,762 --> 01:28:11,093
What are you studying?

1156
01:28:12,298 --> 01:28:14,459
- Art. Yeah.
- Art?

1157
01:28:14,633 --> 01:28:18,091
<i>- Oh, so you're an artist, then?
- Oh. I don't know yet.</i>

1158
01:28:18,537 --> 01:28:19,526
That's great.

1159
01:28:20,873 --> 01:28:22,807
Do you make anything or?

1160
01:28:24,410 --> 01:28:25,399
I don't know yet.

1161
01:28:26,778 --> 01:28:28,575
Well, good luck with that.

1162
01:28:31,316 --> 01:28:32,613
Oh.

1163
01:28:40,024 --> 01:28:41,582
You...

1164
01:28:41,759 --> 01:28:45,922
Would you mind if we walked together
since we're going in the same direction?

1165
01:28:46,096 --> 01:28:49,827
I'll stay on this side of the road.
Don't even have to talk. Just...

1166
01:28:50,667 --> 01:28:54,763
