01:48:06,554 --> 01:48:08,385
Yeah, I know that.

1410
01:48:09,323 --> 01:48:13,725
I know what it is not to feel like you're
in the room until he looks at you...

1411
01:48:13,894 --> 01:48:18,058
...or touches your hand, or even makes
a joke at your expense...

1412
01:48:18,698 --> 01:48:21,166
...just to let everyone know
you're with him.

1413
01:48:21,935 --> 01:48:23,493
You're his.

1414
01:48:25,539 --> 01:48:27,598
God, that man could make me laugh.

1415
01:48:29,408 --> 01:48:30,739
Daddy?

1416
01:48:32,945 --> 01:48:35,175
I don't ever remember you laughing.

1417
01:48:38,918 --> 01:48:41,751
Well, that makes me sad...

1418
01:48:44,957 --> 01:48:46,890
...because I did.

1419
01:48:49,627 --> 01:48:51,356
I did.

1420
01:48:56,868 --> 01:49:00,304
Did you hate Gerry because
he reminded you of Dad?

1421
01:49:02,107 --> 01:49:03,801
A little.

1422
01:49:09,046 --> 01:49:13,540
You know the worst thing for a parent,
second after losing a child?

1423
01:49:15,085 --> 01:49:18,577
Watching your child head for
the same life you had...

1424
01:49:19,490 --> 01:49:21,548
...and you can't stop it.

1425
01:49:24,460 --> 01:49:27,554
It's a terrible, helpless feeling.

1426
01:49:28,831 --> 01:49:31,129
Makes you angry all the time...

1427
01:49:32,568 --> 01:49:34,536
...and I've been angry...

1428
01:49:35,838 --> 01:49:38,169
...a very long time.

1429
01:49:41,309 --> 01:49:42,367
I'm exhausted.

1430
01:49:47,349 --> 01:49:49,374
Do you think we'll ever see Dad again?

1431
01:49:51,253 --> 01:49:53,016
No, sweetheart.

1432
01:49:54,255 --> 01:49:55,882
Never.

1433
01:49:59,193 --> 01:50:01,525
So you have to stop waiting.

1434
01:50:26,186 --> 01:50:27,346
You?

1435
01:50:29,988 --> 01:50:34,220
I have to say I was impressed by how
he worked everything out ahead of time...

1436
01:50:35,260 --> 01:50:38,252
...every delivery schedule,
the mailbox key...

1437
01:50:39,731 --> 01:50:42,700
Getting that leather jacket out
of your apartment wasn't easy...

1438
01:50:42,868 --> 01:50:45,199
...with you acting like Miss Havisham.

1439
01:50:49,807 --> 01:50:51,536
He made me promise.

1440
01:50:52,510 --> 01:50:54,205
I couldn't say no.

1441
01:50:54,912 --> 01:50:58,905
I told him I didn't think
it was good for you, but...

1442
01:50:59,584 --> 01:51:01,415
...I couldn't say no.

1443
01:51:05,755 --> 01:51:07,382
It's the last one...

1444
01:51:12,362 --> 01:51:14,227
...so all alone or not...

1445
01:51:15,699 --> 01:51:17,564
...you gotta walk ahead.

1446
01:51:22,438 --> 01:51:24,497
Thing to remember is...

1447
01:51:25,241 --> 01:51:30,235
...if we're all alone,
then we're all together in that too.

1448
01:51:33,048 --> 01:51:35,516
It helps me sometimes.

1449
01:52:37,942 --> 01:52:40,502
<i>Hi, it's Daniel.</i>

1450
01:52:40,679 --> 01:52:44,978
<i>Remember what I said in the restaurant?
Well, please forget it word by word.</i>

1451
01:52:46,417 --> 01:52:48,783
<i>They're gonna build
a new Yankee stadium.</i>

1452
01:52:49,653 --> 01:52:53,020
<i>I don't know why I said that.
I'm making small talk. I hate small talk.</i>

1453
01:52:53,190 --> 01:52:57,627
<i>I hate the people who make small talk.
I should... I should stop. I'm stopping.</i>

1454
01:52:57,795 --> 01:52:58,784
<i>Shit!</i>

1455
01:53:10,306 --> 01:53:11,898
Gerry?

1456
01:53:17,446 --> 01:53:20,279
My uncle can get us in anytime we want.

1457
01:53:20,949 --> 01:53:23,110
He turned the lights on for us.

1458
01:53:25,721 --> 01:53:27,552
It's amazing...

1459
01:53:55,081 --> 01:53:56,446
You sure?

1460
01:53:58,485 --> 01:54:00,214
It's okay.

1461
01:54:01,921 --> 01:54:05,482
"Dear Holly, I don't have much time.

1462
01:54:05,892 --> 01:54:10,828
I don't mean literally, I mean, you're out
buying ice cream and you'll be home soon...

1463
01:54:11,230 --> 01:54:13,755
...but I have a feeling
this is the last letter.

1464
01:54:13,932 --> 01:54:16,526
Because there's only one thing
left to tell you.

1465
01:54:17,102 --> 01:54:20,162
It isn't to go down memory lane
or make you buy a lamp.

1466
01:54:20,339 --> 01:54:23,502
You can take care of yourself
without any help from me.

1467
01:54:24,643 --> 01:54:29,511
It's to tell you how much you move me.
How you changed me.

1468
01:54:30,281 --> 01:54:33,614
You made me a man
by loving me, Holly...

1469
01:54:33,785 --> 01:54:37,380
...and for that I am eternally grateful.

1470
01:54:37,555 --> 01:54:38,954
Literally.

1471
01:54:40,191 --> 01:54:44,524
If you can promise me anything,
promise me that whenever you're sad...

1472
01:54:44,694 --> 01:54:46,093
<i>:::or unsure:::</i>

1473
01:54:46,763 --> 01:54:49,095
...or you lose complete faith...

1474
01:54:49,866 --> 01:54:52,801
...that you'll try and see yourself
through my eyes.

1475
01:54:53,303 --> 01:54:56,204
Thank you for the honor
of being my wife.

1476
01:54:56,406 --> 01:54:58,704
I'm a man with no regrets.

1477
01:54:58,875 --> 01:55:00,398
How lucky am I?

1478
01:55:01,777 --> 01:55:06,441
You made my life, Holly,
but I'm just one chapter in yours.

1479
01:55:06,816 --> 01:55:08,579
There'll be more.

1480
01:55:09,051 --> 01:55:10,541
I promise.

1481
01:55:11,554 --> 01:55:14,614
So here it comes, the big one.

1482
01:55:16,558 --> 01:55:18,651
Don't be afraid to fall in love again.

1483
01:55:20,261 --> 01:55:24,061
Watch out for that signal
when life as you know it ends.

1484
01:55:26,367 --> 01:55:30,804
P.S., I will always love you. "

1485
01:55:51,290 --> 01:55:53,690
Have you thought about this?

1486
01:55:54,861 --> 01:55:57,091
About me, I mean?

1487
01:55:59,265 --> 01:56:00,926
Have you?

1488
01:56:04,003 --> 01:56:05,630
Yeah.

1489
01:56:31,328 --> 01:56:33,592
- This isn't gonna work, is it?
- No way, no how!

1490
01:56:33,764 --> 01:56:34,924
- Damn!
- Oh!

1491
01:56:37,167 --> 01:56:38,794
Oh, wow.

1492
01:56:39,203 --> 01:56:41,693
I mean, that was like kissing my sister.

1493
01:56:41,871 --> 01:56:44,533
- I'm so relieved!
- Ha-ha-ha.

1494
01:56:44,707 --> 01:56:48,268
I got this letter and I thought he must
have been feeling self-sacrificing...

1495
01:56:48,444 --> 01:56:51,436
...but he's really full of crap.
If he meant it, he'd give me a sign.

1496
01:56:51,614 --> 01:56:54,845
- I hate signs.
- Then I got your message on the machine.

1497
01:57:01,390 --> 01:57:04,120
Weird, bitter friends?

1498
01:57:05,894 --> 01:57:07,657
Forever.

1499
01:57:19,774 --> 01:57:21,537
What's wrong, friend?

1500
01:57:21,709 --> 01:57:23,677
It's Gerry.

1501
01:57:25,680 --> 01:57:27,511
It's been a year...

1502
01:57:29,850 --> 01:57:32,716
...and I don't feel him
around me anymore.

1503
01:57:34,721 --> 01:57:37,019
I don't think he's here anymore.

1504
01:57:39,526 --> 01:57:41,721
I think Gerry's gone.

1505
01:57:43,263 --> 01:57:44,890
He's really gone.

1506
01:58:04,149 --> 01:58:06,582
<i>Dear Gerry, you said you wanted me...</i>

1507
01:58:06,751 --> 01:58:08,184
<i>...to fall in love again...</i>

1508
01:58:08,353 --> 01:58:12,756
<i>...and maybe one day I will,
but there are all kinds of love out there.</i>

1509
01:58:13,958 --> 01:58:15,755
<i>This is my one and only life...</i>

1510
01:58:16,160 --> 01:58:19,618
<i>...and it's a great and terrible
and short and endless thing...</i>

1511
01:58:19,797 --> 01:58:22,594
<i>...and none of us come out of it alive.</i>

1512
01:58:32,442 --> 01:58:37,072
<i>I don't have a plan except
that it's time my mom laughed again.</i>

1513
01:58:37,280 --> 01:58:39,111
<i>She's never seen the world.</i>

1514
01:58:39,282 --> 01:58:45,277
<i>She's never seen Ireland, so I'm
taking her back to where we started.</i>

1515
01:58:51,527 --> 01:58:53,893
<i>Maybe now she'll understand.</i>

1516
01:59:02,437 --> 01:59:03,631
Mom?

1517
01:59:19,219 --> 01:59:20,413
William?

1518
01:59:22,322 --> 01:59:23,516
Hello, you.

1519
01:59:26,827 --> 01:59:28,192
You back for another visit?

1520
01:59:29,530 --> 01:59:30,826
How long?

1521
01:59:31,898 --> 01:59:33,456
I don't know.

1522
01:59:35,768 --> 01:59:38,134
Oh, um... This is my mom, Patricia.

1523
01:59:38,571 --> 01:59:40,436
Hello. This is me father, Patsy.

1524
01:59:44,677 --> 01:59:46,542
You've dropped your sweets, luv.

1525
01:59:46,713 --> 01:59:48,703
Mustn't do that around these parts.

1526
01:59:48,880 --> 01:59:52,475
Pretty woman like you,
a fella could take it the wrong way.

1527
02:00:10,468 --> 02:00:12,026
So I'll see you around, then?

1528
02:00:13,104 --> 02:00:14,537
Yeah.

1529
02:00:21,343 --> 02:00:25,245
<i>I don't know how you did it,
but you brought me back from the dead.</i>

1530
02:00:25,414 --> 02:00:27,439
<i>I'll write to you again soon.</i>

1531
02:00:27,616 --> 02:00:29,481
<i>P. S...</i>

1532
02:00:29,651 --> 02:00:31,312
<i>Guess what.</i>

